genresAdvancedInfo.name: classic australian country
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Classic Australian country is a genre of music that emerged in Australia in the 1920s and 1930s. It is characterized by its use of acoustic guitars, banjos, and fiddles, as well as its focus on the stories and experiences of rural Australians. Classic Australian country often features themes of love, loss, and the struggles of life in the outback.
